From 09ac662caaa47b748cd1cd6d5ac5c017879cd2c9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter Chen <peter.chen@freescale.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Oct 2014 14:59:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0951/1074] MLK-9742-4 usb: chipidea: imx: delete WARN_ON
 message at system suspend

If the core driver's probe has failed(eg, no role is supported), this
WARN_ON will be triggered, the user may think the error occurs.

Acked-by: Li Jun <b47624@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Chen <peter.chen@freescale.com>
[Original patch taken from git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git]
Signed-off-by: Biyao Zhai <biyao.zhai@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/usb/chipidea/ci_hdrc_imx.c |    3 +--
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/chipidea/ci_hdrc_imx.c b/drivers/usb/chipidea/ci_hdrc_imx.c
index 4c1886f..e57e269 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/chipidea/ci_hdrc_imx.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/chipidea/ci_hdrc_imx.c
@@ -531,8 +531,7 @@ static int ci_hdrc_imx_suspend(struct device *dev)
 {
 	struct ci_hdrc_imx_data *data = dev_get_drvdata(dev);
 	int ret;
-	/* The core should make sure the controller is active now */
-	WARN_ON(data->in_lpm);
+
 	if (data->in_lpm)
 		/* The core's suspend doesn't run */
 		return 0;
